gomodel:SYNGO_1260  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this paper, Cazares et al demonstrate a novel function of tomosyn-1 despite its effect on synaptic vesicle priming and ternary complex assembly.\nThe authors monitor the dynamics of distinct synaptic vesicle pools via Vglut1-PhLuorin fluorescence measurements under Wt and tomosyn-1 KD conditions. They demonstrate by quantitative SV pool size measurement the redistribution of vesicles between total releasable pool, TRP (TRP= RRP (readily releasable pool) plus RP (recycling pool)) plus resting pool, ResP (Fig. 1,2). This activity-dependent mechanism of tomosyn-1 consists of clamping of SVs in the ResP and preventing them from transition in the TRP, a function which is regulated by Cdk5-mediated phosphorylation of tomosyn 1. Furthermore, the authors show that tomosyn operates by phosphorylation-dependent association with Rab3a-GTP and synapsin.. Experimental description: Materials and Method:\n\nPrimary hippocampal neuronal culture and transfections/infections.\nNeuronal cultures were prepared from postnatal day 1-2 rat hippocampi of either sex as previously reported (Jakawich et al., 2010)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1260" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

